            <title>[JCR-2981] Bundle of events may be dropped due to NP.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-2981</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>In [1], if the resolver fails to lookup a node entry, a NP is thrown. This exception will break the loop which forwards the events to the observer in [2].&lt;br/&gt;
This will result in an observer not receiving events that he should have.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
[1] org.apache.jackrabbit.jcr2spi.hierarchy.HierarchyManagerImpl#lookup(ItemId workspaceItemId)&lt;br/&gt;
[2] org.apache.jackrabbit.jcr2spi.WorkspaceManager#onEventReceived(EventBundle[] eventBundles,InternalEventListener[] lstnrs)</description>
